# Socket Server Patterns

## Socket.io Setup

- Use namespaces for logical separation
- Implement proper authentication/authorization
- Handle connection/disconnection gracefully
- Use rooms for grouping clients

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { Server as SocketIOServer } from 'socket.io';
import { Server as HTTPServer } from 'http';

const httpServer = new HTTPServer(app);
const io = new SocketIOServer(httpServer, {
  cors: {
    origin: process.env.ALLOWED_ORIGINS?.split(',') || [],
    credentials: true,
  },
  transports: ['websocket', 'polling'],
});

// Authentication middleware
io.use(async (socket, next) => {
  try {
    const token = socket.handshake.auth.token;
    const user = await verifyToken(token);
    socket.data.user = user;
    next();
  } catch (error) {
    next(new Error('Authentication failed'));
  }
});
```

## Event Handling

- Use typed events with TypeScript
- Validate event data
- Handle errors in event handlers
- Emit typed responses

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
interface ServerToClientEvents {
  message: (data: { id: string; content: string; timestamp: Date }) => void;
  error: (error: { code: string; message: string }) => void;
}

interface ClientToServerEvents {
  joinRoom: (roomId: string, callback: (success: boolean) => void) => void;
  sendMessage: (data: { roomId: string; content: string }) => void;
}

io.on('connection', (socket) => {
  socket.on('joinRoom', async (roomId: string, callback) => {
    try {
      await validateRoomAccess(socket.data.user.id, roomId);
      await socket.join(roomId);
      callback(true);
    } catch (error) {
      callback(false);
      socket.emit('error', { code: 'JOIN_FAILED', message: error.message });
    }
  });
});
```

## Error Handling

- Always handle errors in socket event handlers
- Emit error events to clients
- Log errors server-side
- Disconnect clients on critical errors

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
socket.on('sendMessage', async (data) => {
  try {
    const message = await saveMessage({
      userId: socket.data.user.id,
      ...data,
    });
    
    io.to(data.roomId).emit('message', message);
  } catch (error) {
    logger.error('Failed to send message', { error, socketId: socket.id });
    socket.emit('error', {
      code: 'MESSAGE_FAILED',
      message: 'Failed to send message',
    });
  }
});

socket.on('error', (error) => {
  logger.error('Socket error', { error, socketId: socket.id });
});
```

## Resource Management

- Clean up on disconnect
- Remove from rooms on disconnect
- Limit connection rate
- Implement heartbeat/ping-pong

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
io.on('connection', (socket) => {
  const rooms = new Set<string>();
  
  socket.on('joinRoom', (roomId: string) => {
    socket.join(roomId);
    rooms.add(roomId);
  });
  
  socket.on('disconnect', async () => {
    // Clean up resources
    for (const roomId of rooms) {
      await cleanupRoom(roomId, socket.data.user.id);
    }
    logger.info('Client disconnected', { socketId: socket.id });
  });
  
  // Heartbeat
  const pingInterval = setInterval(() => {
    socket.emit('ping');
  }, 30000);
  
  socket.on('pong', () => {
    // Client is alive
  });
  
  socket.on('disconnect', () => {
    clearInterval(pingInterval);
  });
});
```

## Security

- Validate all incoming data
- Rate limit socket events
- Use authentication middleware
- Sanitize user input
- Implement CORS properly

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import rateLimit from 'socket.io-rate-limit';

const socketRateLimit = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 60 * 1000, // 1 minute
  max: 100, // max events per window
});

io.use(socketRateLimit);

io.use(async (socket, next) => {
  const token = socket.handshake.auth.token;
  if (!token) {
    return next(new Error('Authentication required'));
  }
  
  try {
    const user = await verifyToken(token);
    socket.data.user = user;
    next();
  } catch (error) {
    next(new Error('Invalid token'));
  }
});
```
